# OSI Layers
Layer          Name           Purpose
7          Application        User interaction with applications
6          Presentation       Data formatting/encryption
5          Session            Maintain communication session
4          Transport          Reliable delivery (TCP/UDP)
3          Network            Routing and IP addresses
2          Data Link          MAC addresses and Switching
1          Physical           Cables, signals and hardware


# Key Understanding 
- Data moves from Layer 7 down to Layer 1 when sent.
- The receiving device processes the data from Layer 1 back to Layer 7.


# TCP/IP Model
The TCP/IP model is the practical networking model used on the internet.

TCP/IP Layers

Layer                Function
Application          User services
Transport            TCP/UDP communication 
Internet             IP routing
Network Access       Physical network communication 

Improtant Point
The TCP/IP model is simpler than the OSI model and is used in real-world networking.

IP Addresses and Subnets 
I learned how devices are identified on networks using IP addresses.
Example IPv4 Address 192.168.1.1
Key Concepts 
- Every device needs an IP address.
- Subnetting divides networks into smaller sections.
- Routers use IP addresses to send packets between networks.

# TCP vs UDP
TCP is:
- Reliable 
- Connection-oriented
- Slower but accurate

Used for:
- Website
- File transfers
- SSH

UDP is:
- Faster
- Connectionless
- Less reliable

Used for:
- Streaming
- Gaming
- Voice calls

# Encapsulation 
Encapsulation is the process of wrapping data with protocol information as it moves through network layers.

# Process
Application Data--> Segment--> Packet--> Frame--> Bits.  Each layer adds its own header information before transmission.

